cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a parallel Quicksort algorithm for distributed memory systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a modification to the Quicksort algorithm to reduce the volume of data exchanged.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper compares the performance of the proposed algorithm against other implementations.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper provides a template implementation of the proposed algorithm.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with distributed systems and their control.
